"""Bundled seed corpus — realistic support FAQ + product docs so the demo works offline.

Each entry is (source, text). Swap this for the real CC BY 4.0 dataset
`tarekmasryo/rag-qa-logs-corpus-data` (domains support_faq + product_docs) when you
want 500+ docs — see docs/runbooks/local.md. The corpus below is synthetic but
representative for a software SaaS support assistant.
"""

TENANT = "acme"

# fmt: off
CORPUS: list[tuple[str, str]] = [
    ("FAQ: Password reset", "To reset your password, go to the sign-in page and click 'Forgot password'. Enter your account email and we'll send a reset link valid for 30 minutes. Click the link, choose a new password (at least 12 characters), and sign in. If you don't get the email within 5 minutes, check your spam folder or contact support."),
    ("FAQ: Password reset", "If the password reset link has expired, request a new one from the 'Forgot password' page. Reset links expire after 30 minutes for security. Each link can only be used once; requesting a new one invalidates the previous."),
    ("FAQ: MFA setup", "Enable two-factor authentication from Settings → Security → Two-Factor Authentication. Scan the QR code with an authenticator app such as Google Authenticator or Authy, enter the 6-digit code to confirm, and save your backup codes somewhere safe. You'll need a backup code if you lose your phone."),
    ("FAQ: MFA recovery", "If you lose access to your authenticator device and don't have backup codes, contact support with proof of account ownership. We disable MFA after identity verification, which can take 1-2 business days. Backup codes are the fastest recovery path — store them securely when you first enable MFA."),
    ("FAQ: Billing overview", "Plans are billed monthly or annually. Monthly plans are charged on the same date each month; annual plans are charged once per year with a 15% discount. You can switch between monthly and annual billing from Settings → Billing; the change takes effect at the next renewal."),
    ("FAQ: Invoices", "Past invoices are available under Settings → Billing → Invoices. Each invoice is a PDF you can download or email to your finance team. We include the billing period, plan, seats, taxes, and payment method on every invoice."),
    ("FAQ: Update payment method", "Update your card from Settings → Billing → Payment Method. We accept Visa, Mastercard, and Amex. The change applies to your next invoice; the current period is not re-charged. If a payment fails, we retry after 3 and 7 days before downgrading the account."),
    ("FAQ: Failed payment", "If a payment fails, we email the billing contact and retry after 3 and 7 days. After three failed attempts the account downgrades to the Free plan but your data is preserved for 90 days. Re-add a valid payment method and the account resumes on the next successful charge."),
    ("FAQ: Change plan", "Upgrade or downgrade from Settings → Billing → Plan. Upgrades take effect immediately and we prorate the difference. Downgrades take effect at the next renewal so you keep paid features until the period ends."),
    ("FAQ: Cancel subscription", "Cancel from Settings → Billing → Cancel Subscription. Cancellation stops renewal at the end of the current period — you keep access until then. We don't issue partial refunds for the remaining period but you keep your data in read-only mode for 90 days."),
    ("FAQ: Refund policy", "We issue full refunds within 14 days of an annual purchase if you haven't used premium features beyond a free tier allowance. Monthly plans are non-refundable. Contact support with your invoice number to request a refund; decisions take 3-5 business days."),
    ("FAQ: Seats and users", "Each plan includes a number of seats. Add seats from Settings → Team → Invite. Removing a user frees their seat immediately. If you exceed your seat limit, the next invite prompts you to upgrade or remove a seat."),
    ("FAQ: Roles and permissions", "Roles are Owner, Admin, Editor, and Viewer. Owners can change billing and delete the workspace. Admins manage users and settings but not billing. Editors create and edit content; Viewers are read-only. Assign roles from Settings → Team."),
    ("FAQ: API keys", "Generate API keys from Settings → API Keys. Keys are scoped to your workspace and never expire unless revoked. Store them securely — they grant the same access as your account. Revoke a key instantly from the same page if it leaks."),
    ("FAQ: API rate limits", "API rate limits depend on your plan: Free 60 requests/minute, Pro 600/minute, Enterprise custom. Rate-limited responses return HTTP 429 with a Retry-After header. Use exponential backoff; burst up to 2x is allowed for short windows."),
    ("FAQ: Webhooks", "Configure webhooks from Settings → Webhooks. We POST signed JSON events to your URL; verify the X-Signature header with your webhook secret. We retry failed deliveries up to 5 times over 24 hours, then disable the webhook until you fix it."),
    ("FAQ: Data export", "Export your data from Settings → Data → Export. We produce a JSON or CSV archive of your workspace within 24 hours and email a download link valid for 7 days. Exports include all content and attachments but not audit logs older than 1 year."),
    ("FAQ: Data deletion", "Delete your workspace from Settings → Data → Delete. Deletion is irreversible after a 30-day grace period during which support can restore it. After grace, data is purged from primary and backup storage within 72 hours."),
    ("FAQ: GDPR and DPA", "We are GDPR-compliant and offer a Data Processing Agreement for paid plans. Request the DPA from Settings → Legal → DPA or contact support. EU customer data is stored in the eu-central region by default; region is pinned at signup."),
    ("FAQ: SSO setup", "Single sign-on (SAML 2.0) is available on Enterprise plans. Configure it from Settings → Security → SSO. Provide your IdP metadata URL or upload the XML; we generate the SP entity ID and ACS URL. Test with a single user before enforcing SSO org-wide."),
    ("FAQ: SCIM provisioning", "Enterprise plans support SCIM 2.0 user provisioning from Okta, Azure AD, and Google Workspace. Configure from Settings → Security → SCIM with the provided bearer token and base URL. Deprovisioned users are suspended, not deleted, to preserve their content."),
    ("FAQ: Audit logs", "Audit logs are retained 1 year on Pro and 3 years on Enterprise. View them under Settings → Security → Audit Log. Export to CSV or stream to your SIEM via the audit webhook. Logs capture actor, action, target, IP, and timestamp."),
    ("FAQ: IP allowlist", "Restrict workspace access to known IP ranges from Settings → Security → IP Allowlist (Enterprise). Add CIDR ranges; requests outside them are blocked at sign-in and API. The allowlist applies to all users including owners, so keep an emergency bypass contact with support."),
    ("FAQ: Session timeout", "Sessions expire after 30 days of inactivity by default. Enterprise admins can set a shorter timeout from Settings → Security → Sessions (minimum 1 hour). 'Remember me' extends the session to 90 days on trusted devices."),
    ("FAQ: Mobile app", "Our mobile app is available on iOS and Android. Sign in with the same credentials. Offline edits sync when you reconnect. Push notifications are configurable per workspace under Settings → Notifications."),
    ("FAQ: Email notifications", "Control email notifications from Settings → Notifications. You can set per-channel digest (instant, daily, weekly, off) and mute specific threads. Mention notifications are always instant and cannot be muted."),
    ("FAQ: Slack integration", "Connect Slack from Settings → Integrations → Slack. Authorize the workspace, pick channels to mirror, and set notification filters. Messages sent in Slack mirror back to the app and vice versa; threads stay linked."),
    ("FAQ: Jira integration", "Link Jira from Settings → Integrations → Jira. You can create issues from any item and sync status both ways. The integration uses an API token you generate in Jira; store it in our vault and rotate it quarterly."),
    ("FAQ: GitHub integration", "Connect GitHub from Settings → Integrations → GitHub. Link repos to projects; commits and PRs appear on the timeline. We request read and repo scope only; we never write to your repositories."),
    ("FAQ: Custom fields", "Add custom fields from Settings → Custom Fields. Fields can be text, number, date, or select. They appear on items and are filterable in views. Once a field has data, its type cannot change; archive it instead of deleting."),
    ("FAQ: Views and filters", "Create saved views from any list with filters applied. Views can be shared with the workspace or kept private. Group by any field, sort by multiple columns, and pin views to the sidebar for quick access."),
    ("FAQ: Automations", "Automations run when a trigger fires (status change, date, field value). Add conditions and actions (assign, notify, set field). Automations run in order; a failed action logs an error but doesn't stop later automations. Audit automation runs under Settings → Automations → History."),
    ("FAQ: Webhooks vs automations", "Webhooks notify external systems of events; automations perform in-app actions. Use webhooks to sync to other tools and automations to reduce manual steps inside the app. They compose — an automation can also fire a webhook."),
    ("FAQ: File uploads", "Upload files up to 100 MB per file on Pro and 1 GB on Enterprise. We store files encrypted at rest and scan for malware on upload. Unsupported file types are rejected with a clear message; zip archives are inspected recursively."),
    ("FAQ: Storage limits", "Free plans include 1 GB storage, Pro 50 GB, Enterprise custom. Storage includes attachments and exports. When you approach the limit we email the billing contact; at the limit, uploads are blocked until you upgrade or delete content."),
    ("FAQ: Search", "Search across all content with Ctrl+K. Search respects your permissions — you only see results from items you can access. Use filters to narrow by type, owner, date, or custom field. Search supports exact-phrase quotes and field:value operators."),
    ("FAQ: Version history", "Every item keeps a full version history for 90 days (Pro) or unlimited (Enterprise). Restore any prior version in one click; the restore itself becomes a new version so history is never lost."),
    ("FAQ: Comments and mentions", "@mention a teammate in any comment to notify them instantly. Comments support rich text and attachments. Resolve a comment to collapse it; resolved comments are searchable but don't notify."),
    ("FAQ: Guest access", "Invite guests (external collaborators) from an item's share menu. Guests see only the items they're invited to and can't browse the workspace. Guest seats are billed at a lower rate and capped per plan."),
    ("FAQ: Templates", "Create reusable templates from any item. Templates capture fields, automations, and starter content. Apply a template on creation to standardize workflows. Templates are versioned; applying a template doesn't upgrade existing items."),
    ("Product doc: Getting started", "Getting started: create a workspace, invite your team, and create your first project. Projects hold items; items hold fields, comments, and files. Use views to slice your project; use automations to remove repetitive work. The onboarding checklist in the sidebar walks you through these steps."),
    ("Product doc: Workspaces", "A workspace is the top-level container for your team. Each workspace has its own members, billing, and settings. You can belong to multiple workspaces and switch between them from the workspace menu. Workspaces are isolated — data is never shared across them."),
    ("Product doc: Projects", "Projects group related items. A project has its own views, automations, and members. Archive a project to hide it without deleting its data. Projects can be duplicated to a new workspace for templated rollouts."),
    ("Product doc: Items", "Items are the unit of work. An item has a name, status, assignee, dates, custom fields, comments, and attachments. Every change is versioned. Items can be linked to other items to track dependencies and blockers."),
    ("Product doc: Status workflows", "Define a status workflow per project: the set of statuses and allowed transitions. Transitions can trigger automations. A common workflow is Backlog → In Progress → Review → Done. Statuses are color-coded and filterable."),
    ("Product doc: Permissions model", "Permissions are role-based (Owner/Admin/Editor/Viewer) and refined per project. Project-level permissions can restrict a Viewer to specific projects. Custom roles are available on Enterprise. Permissions are evaluated on every action server-side; client hiding is not a security control."),
    ("Product doc: Security architecture", "All traffic is TLS 1.2+. Data is encrypted at rest with AES-256. Secrets are stored in a managed vault and rotated quarterly. We run pen tests twice a year and maintain a SOC 2 Type II report. Security advisories are published on our trust page."),
    ("Product doc: Availability", "We target 99.9% monthly uptime for paid plans. Status is published at status.example.com with real-time component health and incident history. Maintenance windows are announced at least 72 hours in advance and run in off-peak regional hours."),
    ("Product doc: Backups", "Backups run every 6 hours to a separate region. Point-in-time recovery is available for the last 35 days. Restores are tested monthly. Customer-initiated exports complement our backups and are the recommended path for full data portability."),
    ("Product doc: API authentication", "Authenticate API calls with a bearer token: `Authorization: Bearer <api_key>`. Keys are workspace-scoped. Include `Idempotency-Key` on POST requests to prevent duplicate creates on retry. All API responses are JSON; errors use a consistent {error: {code, message}} shape."),
    ("Product doc: API pagination", "List endpoints return up to 100 items per page and include a `cursor` for the next page. Use `?limit=` up to 100 and `?cursor=` from the previous response. Pages are stable for 24 hours; request a fresh cursor if you iterate longer."),
    ("Product doc: Webhooks events", "We emit events for item.created, item.updated, item.deleted, comment.created, and status.changed. Each event includes the actor, timestamp, and a snapshot of the changed fields. Subscribe to events from Settings → Webhooks; one webhook can subscribe to many event types."),
    ("Product doc: SDKs", "Official SDKs are available for Python, JavaScript/TypeScript, and Go. SDKs wrap the REST API, handle retries with exponential backoff, and refresh tokens. Community SDKs exist for Ruby and PHP but are not maintained by us."),
    ("Product doc: CLI", "The CLI (`app-cli`) lets you script the workspace from a terminal: create items, run automations, and export data. Install via `brew install app-cli` or `pipx install app-cli`. Authenticate with an API key; the CLI never stores your password."),
    ("Product doc: Self-host", "Self-hosted Enterprise is deployable on your own Kubernetes via our Helm chart. You bring Postgres, object storage, and the model runtime. We provide the image, chart, and a runbook. Air-gapped installs are supported; contact sales for licensing."),
    ("Product doc: Data residency", "Choose your data region (US, EU, AU) at workspace creation; it cannot be changed later. Replication stays within the chosen region for compliance. Enterprise customers can request a dedicated region or single-tenant deployment."),
    ("Product doc: Logging and monitoring", "We emit structured logs with request IDs. Customers on Enterprise can forward their audit logs to their SIEM. We do not log request bodies or payloads; we log metadata (endpoint, status, latency, actor) only."),
    ("Product doc: Incident response", "On a confirmed incident we page the on-call engineer, create a status entry within 15 minutes, and post updates every 30 minutes until resolved. Post-incident we publish a blameless postmortem within 5 business days on our trust page."),
    ("Product doc: Support channels", "Support is available via in-app chat (all plans), email (Pro+), and priority Slack with a 1-hour SLA (Enterprise). Include your workspace slug and a reproducible description. Attach screenshots or a HAR file for faster resolution."),
    ("Product doc: Account closure", "Closing your account cancels all plans and schedules deletion after a 30-day grace period. Download an export before closure if you want to keep your data. Closure is irreversible after the grace period; support cannot restore it."),
    ("Product doc: Trusted devices", "A trusted device skips MFA for 30 days after you mark it. You can review and revoke trusted devices from Settings → Security → Sessions. Revoke immediately if a device is lost or stolen; this forces MFA on the next sign-in."),
    ("Product doc: Email domain verification", "Verify your email domain from Settings → Security → Domains to enable auto-join for your team. Users signing in with a verified domain email are auto-added to the workspace up to your seat limit. Unverified users require manual invite."),
]
